	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June 5617</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">The <date>June</date> Occident first<lb/> received informs me of your having entered<lb/> once more into the active duties of the<lb/> ministry&#44; and although you may be said<lb/> to have never wholly relinquished them&#44; yet<lb/> I warmly congratulate you on your<lb/> becoming Hazan of the Synagogue Beth El Emeth<lb/> Minhag sephardim to which with all my<lb/> heart I wish the fullest possible amount<lb/> of success and prosperity.  You may think<lb/> me tardy in expressing these wishes&#44; but<lb/> recollect&#44; dear sir&#44; the first notification<lb/> I had from you of the event&#44; was your<lb/> article in the <date>June</date> Occident.  True&#44; <persName>Miss<lb/> Sarah Joseph</persName> mentioned to me in your<lb/> name that the Synagogue would probably be<lb/> opened for <add>Hebrew</add>&#59; at which I of course<lb/> expressed my gratification.  And believe me<lb/> that for your sake I was much pleased<lb/> to hear of the movement.  As to the absurd</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>objection that there is no room<lb/> for two Portuguese synagogues&#8212;this is<lb/> more astonishing than annoying.  When<lb/> <sic>hundred</sic> of German &#38; Polish Congregations<lb/> are formed under the most unpromising<lb/> auspices&#44; why in the name of reason should<lb/> we not multiply&#8212;or attempt to multiply<lb/> congregations having so superior a ritual<lb/> as the Portuguese.  I sincerely believe the<lb/> greatest blow to wild reform among<lb/> the German &#38; Polish Kehilloth is the<lb/> introduction of the minhag sephardim<lb/> among congregations who cannot <add>&#63;</add><lb/> long troublesome Peyutim Keroboth &#38;c<lb/> I will not trouble you however with<lb/> a long disquisition on a theme you have<lb/> yourself often pronounced on.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You have no doubt heard of<lb/> the death of a very valued old friend<lb/> of mine&#8212;and correspondent of the Occident<lb/> <persName>Mr. J. Peynado</persName> of <placeName>Hackney&#44; England</placeName>&#44;<lb/> As my father writes me&#8212;He was one<lb/> of the last <hi rend="underline">real</hi> &#40;Portuguese&#41; <hi rend="underline">gentlemen</hi><lb/> for which K. K. <add>&#63;</add> <placeName>London</placeName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>was celebrated.  The material of the <add>Hebrew</add> is<lb/> yet not had&#44; but new like <persName>Jo Peynardo</persName><lb/> one does not meet with every day.  To know<lb/> him was to love him.  Truly religious &#40;altho&#44;<lb/> having as you know peculiar views of some<lb/> matters&#41; he was strictly honorable&#44; urbane<lb/> and charitable.  His zeal for his religion often<lb/> as you well know&#44; led him to take up the<lb/> pen&#44; and he even administered a pretty<lb/> severe castigation to <persName>Dr McCaul</persName> in defense of<lb/> <persName>Miss Aguilar</persName>.  I have no doubt you have<lb/> some materials for an obituary notice of<lb/> him in the Occident.  He deserves one <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I perceive <persName>Jacobs</persName> of <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> has resigned.  The Israelite who wanted to<lb/> say something bitter and could not <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> says it is one disease of the system of<lb/> the orthodoxy.  Do you know any other<lb/> reason for I expect there must be another.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">When do you commence the &#8220;Advocate&#63;<lb/>  <persName>Mrs DeSola</persName> desires me to congratulate<lb/> you in her name on your resumption<lb/> of clerical duties&#44; and she wishes you<lb/> as do I&#44; many years of happiness<lb/> in their discharge.  I shall be very</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>glad to hear from you when you<lb/> have leisure&#44; and believe me as ever</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Yours faithfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
		</body>
